{
  "doc_id": "8243",
  "text": "Nucleosomes were assembled using purified octamers (recombinant X. laevis or chicken) and polyglutamic acid (PGA; Sigma P4886) according to [CITATION_1] . PGA and histones were mixed in a 2:1 ratio in 150 mM NaCl and incubated for 1-2 h at room temperature. Precipitates were removed by centrifugation and the supernatant (HP-mix) was stored at 4 °C. Different ratios of 32 P-body labeled DNA (Widom 601 sequence, 161 nt) and HP-mix were empirically tested to reveal the optimal conditions for nucleosome assembly. Nucleosomes were separated by native polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis (4.5% polyacrylamide, 0.25x TBE, 5% glycerol), assembled nucleosomes were cut out and eluted from the gel.",
